<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>shelly action on Shelly CLI</title><link>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/action/</link><description>Recent content in shelly action on Shelly CLI</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-US</language><atom:link href="https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/action/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>shelly action clear</title><link>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/action/clear/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/action/clear/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="shelly-action-clear"&gt;shelly action clear&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clear an action URL for a Gen1 device&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="synopsis"&gt;Synopsis&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clear (remove) an action URL for a Gen1 Shelly device.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This removes the configured URL for the specified action, disabling the
HTTP callback for that event.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gen1 devices support various action event types:
Output events: out_on_url, out_off_url
Button events: btn1_on_url, btn1_off_url, btn2_on_url, btn2_off_url
Input events: input_on_url, input_off_url
Push events: longpush_url, shortpush_url, double_shortpush_url, triple_shortpush_url
Roller events: roller_open_url, roller_close_url, roller_stop_url
Sensor events: motion_url, no_motion_url, flood_detected_url, etc.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>shelly action list</title><link>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/action/list/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/action/list/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="shelly-action-list"&gt;shelly action list&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;List action URLs for a Gen1 device&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="synopsis"&gt;Synopsis&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;List all configured action URLs for a Gen1 Shelly device.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gen1 devices support various action types that trigger HTTP callbacks:&lt;/p&gt;
