&lt;p&gt;Set an action URL for a Gen1 device&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="synopsis"&gt;Synopsis&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Set an action URL for a Gen1 Shelly device.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gen1 devices support various action event types:
Output events: out_on_url, out_off_url
Button events: btn1_on_url, btn1_off_url, btn2_on_url, btn2_off_url
Input events: input_on_url, input_off_url
Push events: longpush_url, shortpush_url, double_shortpush_url, triple_shortpush_url
Roller events: roller_open_url, roller_close_url, roller_stop_url
Sensor events: motion_url, no_motion_url, flood_detected_url, etc.
System events: overpower_url, overvoltage_url, overtemperature_url&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gen2+ devices use webhooks instead. See &amp;lsquo;shelly webhook create&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>shelly action test</title><link>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/action/test/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/action/test/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="shelly-action-test"&gt;shelly action test&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Test/trigger an action on a Gen1 device&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="synopsis"&gt;Synopsis&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Test (trigger) an action on a Gen1 Shelly device.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This simulates the event that would trigger the action URL, causing
the device to make the configured HTTP request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gen1 devices trigger actions based on actual state changes. This command
will temporarily change the device state to trigger the action callback.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For output actions (out_on_url, out_off_url), the device relay will be toggled.
For button actions, the physical button press must be used.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>